Thread Safety kya hoti hai?

Definition
A class or code is Thread Safe if multiple threads can access it simultaneously without producing incorrect or inconsistent results.(without entering into race conditions or data corruption)
Achieved using:

synchronized
ReentrantLock
Atomic Classes (AtomicInteger)
Immutable Objects (String)

Thread Pool
A collection of pre-created worker threads used to execute tasks.
Threads are reused instead of creating a new thread for every task.
Reduces thread creation overhead and improves performance.
Tasks wait in a queue if all threads are busy.
Commonly implemented using Executor Framework (ExecutorService).
Used internally by Spring Boot/Tomcat to handle multiple HTTP requests efficiently.

